//PATTERN-2 Rearrangement / In-place manipulation

//* Move all the zeros to the last


//PROBLEM STATEMENT ---

/*

Problem

You are given an integer array nums.
Your task is to move all zeroes to the end of the array while maintaining the relative order of non-zero elements.
Important:
The operation must be performed in-place, without using an extra array.

Function Declaration
Function Name: moveZeroes

Description:
This function moves all zeroes to the end of the array while keeping the order of non-zero elements unchanged.

Parameters
nums → reference to an integer array
(contains both zero and non-zero elements)

Return Value
The function returns void
The array must be modified in-place

Constraints
1 ≤ nums.length ≤ 10⁴
-2³¹ ≤ nums[i] ≤ 2³¹ - 1


Input Format
The first line contains an integer T — number of test cases
For each test case:
First line contains N — size of the array
Second line contains N space-separated integers

Output Format
For each test case, print the modified array after moving all zeroes to the end.
If there are no zeroes, print the array as it is.

Sample Input
3
7
4 0 5 0 0 7 8
5
0 2 0 0 9
1
3

Sample Output
4 5 7 8 0 0 0
2 9 0 0 0
3

Explanation

Test Case 1
Array: 4 0 5 0 0 7 8
After moving zeroes:
4 5 7 8 0 0 0

Test Case 2
Array: 0 2 0 0 9
After moving zeroes:
2 9 0 0 0

Test Case 3
Array: 3
No zeroes present, so it remains:
3

*/

//SOLUTION----

/*
class Solution {
    public void moveZeroes(int[] nums) {
        // write your code here
       int insertpos =0;
    // now mai non zero integers ko aage karunga 
    for (int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
        if(nums[i]!=0){
            nums[insertpos]=nums[i];
            insertpos++;
        }
    }
    //rest elements ko zero set kar dunga 😎🥳...wohoooo
    while(insertpos<nums.length){
        nums[insertpos]=0;
        insertpos++;
    }
    }
}
*/
